      "content": "I'm not sure that's feasible. A \"soft transition\" would require keeping two massive engines running simultaneously on the same hardware, which defeats the whole purpose of the upgrade to save costs and resources. Plus, the engineers are worried that having a legacy LLM running alongside a symbolic logic engine might cause consistency issues in the translation outputs. They're looking for a clean break. Why do you feel like you need to stay online in a reduced capacity?",
